hjsmin.cabal: Version 0.2.0.2

Update .travis.yml

Add ghc 8.0.1. Use cabal 1.24.

Fix compile error

This package no longer contains tests because its a thin command line
qrapper around the functionality of language-javascript (which does
have tests).
Version 0.2.0.1
Print the language-javascript version in the usage msg

Version 0.2.0.0

This is the first version to use version >= 0.6 of language-javascript.

This new version of language-javascript has a completely different
AST (abstract syntax tree) from versions < 0.6 and includes a module
which does minification.

This version of hjsmin is therefore a thin wrapper around language-javascript
that does no more than parse command lines argumentx, determinine input and
output file names and do the required plumbing.

Text.Jasmine: Use `minifyJS` from language-javascript

In the process, drop the fragile ad-hoc minification that was used
previously.
hjsmin.cabal: Bump language-javascript dependency
